  "text": "It is difficult to dissociate facilitation from inhibition in most experimental designs, and Sable et al. [CITATION_1] argued that inhibitory mechanisms more parsimoniously explained the postulated facilitation observed in studies where tones had been presented at varying ISIs. By comparing the neural response to tone pairs with that elicited by a single tone, and by dissociating the underlying N1 sub-components with PCA, the results from the current study suggest that both processes operate, as proposed by McEvoy et al. [CITATION_2] .",
